Package sets

Interface Set<E>

Type Parameters:
E - the type of elements in this set
All Superinterfaces:
Collection<E>, Iterable<E>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractSet, ArrayListSet, ArraySet
public interface Set<E> extends Collection<E>
Interface defining what a set is: - A set is a collection of elements without duplicates and null elements in which the order of the elements does not matter (for comparing purposes): e.g. two sets containing the same elements in different order are considered to be equals - Furthermore a set defines several set operations such as - union - intersection - difference - symetric difference
Author:
David Roussel and Aiglon Dor√©
